modules.description: Provides routing, request handling, and response generation for web applications using simple function definitions. Works with HTTP methods, URL paths, and structured data types like records and variants for request and response bodies. Enables building RESTful APIs and dynamic web pages with minimal setup and configuration.

The module provides HTTP request/response handling, cookie and session management, CSRF protection, and middleware composition, operating on request objects, response streams, and session data to enable secure web interactions. It supports form validation, WebSocket communication, and template rendering, with use cases including secure authentication, stateful session management, and integrating GraphQL or SQL databases. Key data structures include HTTP status/method types, session dictionaries, and stream handlers, alongside utilities for logging, error handling, and URL encoding.
